  "prompt": "Are there legal obligations for financial institutions regarding money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, financial institutions have significant legal obligations to prevent money laundering, including:\n\n1. Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Verifying customer identities\n- Conducting background checks\n- Monitoring suspicious transactions\n\n2. Reporting requirements\n- Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Reporting cash transactions over certain thresholds\n- Maintaining transaction records\n\n3. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) compliance programs\n- Implementing internal control procedures\n- Training staff on detecting potential money laundering\n- Conducting regular risk assessments\n\n4. Legal regulations\n- Compliance with Bank Secrecy Act\n- Following Financial Action Task Force (FATF) guidelines\n- Adhering to international anti-money laundering standards\n\n5. Penalties for non-compliance\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential criminal charges\n- Loss of banking licenses\n\nThese obligations are designed to prevent criminals from using financial systems to disguise illegal funds and maintain financial system integrity.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
